# What is HTTP?

**HTTP (HyperText Transfer Protocol)** is an application-layer protocol used for communication between a **client** (browser, mobile app, Postman, React app) and a **server** (backend application such as Django, Flask, Node.js, etc.).

Whenever you open a website or call an API, HTTP is used to transfer requests and responses.


## HTTP Communication Flow

```text
Browser (Client)
      |
      | HTTP Request
      V
Backend Server
      |
      | HTTP Response
      V
Browser (Client)
```

### Example

You open:

```text
http://example.com
```

The browser sends an HTTP request.

The server processes the request and returns:

* HTML
* CSS
* JavaScript
* Images
* JSON Data


---
# Real-Life Example

Imagine ordering food.

```text
You (Client)
      |
      | Order Pizza (Request)
      V
Restaurant (Server)
      |
      | Pizza Delivered (Response)
      V
You (Client)
```

HTTP works exactly the same way.


