# HTTP Methods

These are the most important HTTP methods for backend development and interviews.

| Method | Purpose                 | Example         |
| ------ | ----------------------- | --------------- |
| GET    | Read Data               | Get all users   |
| POST   | Create Data             | Create new user |
| PUT    | Replace Entire Resource | Update profile  |
| PATCH  | Update Partial Resource | Change password |
| DELETE | Delete Resource         | Delete account  |


---
# 1. GET Method

Used to fetch data.

Example Request

```http
GET /users
```

Example Response

```json
[
    {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Rahul"
    },
    {
        "id": 2,
        "name": "Priya"
    }
]
```

## Flask Example

```python
from flask import Flask, jsonify

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/users", methods=["GET"])
def get_users():
    return jsonify([
        {"id": 1, "name": "Rahul"},
        {"id": 2, "name": "Priya"}
    ])

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)
```

Output

```json
[
    {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Rahul"
    },
    {
        "id": 2,
        "name": "Priya"
    }
]
```


---
# 2. POST Method

Used to create new data.

Request

```http
POST /users
```

Body

```json
{
    "name": "Rahul"
}
```

## Flask Example

```python
from flask import Flask, request, jsonify

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/users", methods=["POST"])
def create_user():
    data = request.get_json()

    return jsonify({
        "message": "User Created",
        "user": data
    })

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True)
```

Output

```json
{
    "message": "User Created",
    "user": {
        "name": "Rahul"
    }
}
```


